item.title: Austin's song Float re-created on Drumpads24
item.dc:creator: Auxy
item.description:
Seems to me like this is some random guy who has made this for some competition they’re running or something. Obviously not ok to use the content without any attribution or correct license. Not sure if it’s worth bothering about though.

Since @aUstin_Haga is the rights owner, he’s the one that can take action if he wants to. I would potentially report the video on YouTube and you have an option to send a “cease and desist” letter to the company if they are hosting any content that you own the copyright of. The latter action is probably not worth the effort though, unless the track really blows up and starts generating revenue for them.

The company seems to have a lot of followers but not any proper user terms or similar with contact details for these matters.
